cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.IR, cs.CYBER, cs.HC 

This paper focuses on predicting real-world talk attendances at academic conferences using machine learning methods. The paper analyzes and discusses the predictive power of contact and interest networks separately and in combination. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Additionally, the paper also discusses user interests extracted from their previous publications, which falls under the sub-category cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The paper also deals with analyzing and predicting human behavior, which can be categorized under cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences). The paper also discusses the use of machine learning methods, which can be categorized under cs.CYBER (Cybernetics) and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
